column1: # Name: Net enrollment ratio in pre-primary school, male

# Definition: The number of children enrolled in pre-primary school who belong to the age group that officially corresponds to pre-primary schooling, divided by the total population of the same age group.
# Source: UN Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) Institute for Statistics
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
